td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usimanmistrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SimanMistrunner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 119<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/1/02 11:49:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2220.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Rogue Advice</span><hr size=1> I have spent most of my Everquest life playing a druid (my 3 characters past 20 have all been a druid) and am very familiar with the class and online resources for druids.  After 55 seasons on my current druid, I realized that I was bored out of my mind with being a druid and needed a change of pace.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, I created a rogue and really enjoy the life of a melee character; granted he is only level 14 at the moment.  He is somewhat twinked and, accordingly, I have been able to level easily by soloing up to this point.  However, I know rogues are a grouping class and fully realize I will not level to 60 via soloing.  I really want to be able to learn more about the class.<br>
<br>
I am starting to realize that many of the sites that gave great information on druids (eqdruids and casterrealm) do not have similar information for rogues--or at least particularly helpful information.  I am just now able to duel wield but notice my primary piercer accounts for about 90% of the hits against mobs while my secondary slasher accounts for about 10% of the hits.  I hope that will improve as my duel wielding goes up.  At level 16, I get double attack and I understand that gives me a chance to hit twice as opposed to once per swing.  I have been told that, at later levels, I will want to have proficiency in 1hs for offhand and I have decided to use a 1hs in my secondary to keep that skill up.  To be honest, there are some other things I have no clue about:  making poisons, picking locks, sensing traps, instill fear, etc.<br>
<br>
My question is are there any helpful sites out there tailored to rogues and where one can read about rogue abilities, etc.?<br>
<br>
Thanks.<br>
<br>
Sadistik<br>
Level 14 Rogue<br>
