<br>
I have a 44 Vah Shir rogue on a different server, and have some advice:<br>
<br>
1] Soloing becomes impossible really fast, simply due to the fact that you need access to a mobs back to backstab, and when you're soloing the mob faces you. End of story. Instill doubt is functionally useless in terms of fear kiting; for every time it works, there will be a number of times it doesnt. You'll end up dead a lot of those times.<br>
<br>
2] Strength is where its at baby. Id put any remaining points into stamina. This is because...<br>
<br>
3] ...as a rogue, your purpose in 99.9% of groups will be to do as much damage in as little time as you can.  Strength helps the most with that. Invest all of your resources into getting the best weapons you possibly can, because armor for rogues is a joke no matter what level or quality, so dont worry about it. You want a piercer with high damage (for backstabs) but a good damage/delay ratio (for overall damage) in your primary slot; I used a high damage 1hs in my secondary slot, simply because its easier to find high damage 1hs than it is to find high damage 1hp.<br>
<br>
4] Pick locks is useful 50+. You can use the doors in Befallen to practise your skill up, but beware: if you wait to do it all at once, even if you hotkey it, it will take you a LONG time to raise it. It took me 5 hours of *clickclickclick* to get my rogue from 1 to 194. I suggest renting a few movies and giving your wrist a rest every so often.<br>
<br>
5] LEARN TO AVOID AGGRO. *smiles* Evade is the &quot;hide&quot; skill when used in combat. Make a habit of using it *before* you aggro the mob onto you... It drops you on the hate list even if the mob hasnt turned on you yet; at higher levels, if you aggro mobs at all, you'll get mauled. As I mentioned earlier, rogue armor resembles saran wrap in a lot of ways...<br>
<br>
Thats my &quot;off-the-top-of-my-head&quot; advice. If you have any questions about anything, feel free to send me a tell in game.<br>
