<br>
Having a misspelled word for a name doesn't make you 1337, or whatever you were trying to prove with that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 848<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 1:14:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2220.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I almost forgot</span><hr size=1> First off, rangers are your best friends.  They fear animals and snare for kiting, and their attack buffs at high level will be a blast.   Woo woo!<br>
<br>
And my general advice:<br>
<br>
First off, rogues CAN solo.  It's just far less efficient than grouping for us.  Instill Doubt will be your best friend outdoors, once you learn to use it (hint, you can't backstab and ID at the same time).<br>
<br>
Two, agro is your friend.  Rogues have enourmous controll over it... you can evade to lose agro, beg and disarm and backstab to gain it.  Remember, you're not a tank, but you're not an int caster either.  You want to be just under the tanks on the agro list... it's better for the mob to be on you than the cleric, and you have the best evasion AC in the game.  Just keep that defense skill up.<br>
<br>
Three, usually one wants to put your points into stamina when creating the character, but then max strength until it's hitting 255 when buffed, then switch to AC and HP gear.  Keep your dex up too.<br>
<br>
Four, you won't do much damage early on, but as you level, you start to have more fun.  Backstab is a real blessing.<br>
<br>
Five, sneak and hide... learn them well.  They're nothing like Chamo.  They are way better.  Con everything while you sneak about, you're the masters of CR except in certain zones.<br>
<br>
Six, remember that rogues can do almost anything.  We CAN tank a bit, we can pull effectively, and we can do a lot more... just work with it!<br>
<br>
Jarkell Ravensteel<br>
