<br>
With all due respect... I found soloing a rogue to be one of the most time consuming undertakings possible in the game. Can it be done? Possibly, if you hunt the zone lines, have excellent equipment, and invest in a lot of sow potions. That requires a ton of money though, and its still a risky undertaking.<br>
<br>
My rogue had massive AC for a chain-class, did some tanking with groups in OT (ie, had defense maxed), and still got **mauled** by blues when I had to tank them face to face.<br>
<br>
For a variety of reasons. Instill Doubt isnt like a fear spell--it isnt reliable at all. When it doesnt work, you get mauled. When you get an add, you get mauled. The only snare you have access to is a proc off a specific weapon, so to fear kite alone you have to rely on the proc and the ID working in conjunction... If the fight gets ugly, you have no means of escape, unless you're sowed or at a zone. Plus, once the fight is over, you have no access to healing, beyond bandaids. <br>
<br>
So to summarize what I found: rogues struggle fighting face to face, cant escape quickly, cant deal with adds at all, cant consistently fear and/or snare on their own, and cant heal. Thats why I dont suggest soloing.<br>
<br>
Is it possible? I suppose. Anything is possible if you dont mind 20 minutes of downtime between fights, although at higher levels the experience loss from even a single unrezed death an evening might very well make it beyond pursuing.<br>
<br>
Is it advisable? Not from where I stand... If you dont believe me, try it and find out. I did. It hurt.<br>
<br>
But thats just me.<br>
